content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #79009 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
I think we should wait to see whether this is actually a regression or the test just breaks on gdb 10

my understanding is that tests are actually failing on gdb 10.1, or I am misreading the issue?

But I don't have exactly clear which piece of software is failing. Would asking for a smaller repro out of their testsuite for debuginfo-gdb make sense? Seems like more than one reason could be involved (those failing tests seems to indicate various and unrelated things being tested).
P-medium in the sense that we should probably fix it eventually, but I don't think this is actually a regression
